com.gl.vn.me.ko.pies.base.config

Interface PropsConfig

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    XmlPropsConfig

    @ThreadSafe
public interface PropsConfig
    Represents a configuration that consists of properties.

    A property is an entity that is identified by PropertyName and MAY have a value. Value of a property MUST be consistent with the PropertyType. A value of a property MAY be treated as some other PropertyType if it's possible to convert the value to that type. A property can either be single or multiple. Single properties MAY only have a single value and multiple properties MAY have multiple values.

    A property is undefined if it is not specified in the configuration or its value is null.
